@node "Credits" "Credits"

Assampler takes full advantage of these projects (an important point of what I consider as efficient programming and the way of Amiga programming in general):
@{b}function libraries@{ub} - the things you will use, when starting Assampler
@{u}MUI (MagicUserInterface)@{uu}, Stefan Stuntz, user interface
@{u}MCC_Listtree@{uu}, Klaus Melchior, Mui-Custom-Class to display tree structures
@{u}AHI (AudioHardwareInterface)@{uu}, Martin Blom, device independent sound input and output
@{u}datatypes (V45)@{uu}, Christian Buchner/Roland Mainz, Import/Export in several file formats
@{u}ReqTools@{uu}, Nico François + Magnus Holmgren, requesters
@{u}Cluster-OFunctions.mod@{uu}, Viona, formula interpreter
@{u}iffparse@{uu}, AmigaOS3.1
@{u}SearchGuide, LSAGS@{uu}, search routine for AmigaGuides

@{b}development environment@{ub} - the things I developed Assampler with
@{u}Cluster@{uu}, Viona/MOM, programming language (excellent extension of ModulaII)
@{u}PhxAss@{uu}, Frank Wille, Assembler (the right spelling for this word :-)
@{u}ADis@{uu}, Martin Apel, Disassembler
@{u}KingCon@{uu}, David Larsson, "only" a Console handler, but simplifies programming work a lot

and much others ...

@endnode

